title: TidyTuesday #2
text:
Data was sourced from US Egg Production Data by jonthegeek on Github

# Packages
library(tidyverse)
library(ggplot2)

# Data
eggproduction  <- readr::read_csv('https://raw.githubusercontent.com/rfordatascience/tidytuesday/master/data/2023/2023-04-11/egg-production.csv')


# Filter by year
eggproduction |>
  select(observed_month, n_hens, n_eggs) |>
  filter(str_starts(as.character(observed_month), "2020"))

# A tibble: 48 × 3
   observed_month   n_hens     n_eggs
   <date>            <dbl>      <dbl>
 1 2020-01-31     64019000 1221400000
 2 2020-02-29     64384000 1154100000
 3 2020-03-31     64730000 1239900000
 4 2020-04-30     65044000 1203500000
 5 2020-05-31     64481000 1239100000
 6 2020-06-30     64251000 1207400000
 7 2020-07-31     64353000 1255200000
 8 2020-08-31     64223000 1257100000
 9 2020-09-30     63975000 1219800000
10 2020-10-31     63728000 1254800000
# ℹ 38 more rows

# Plotting
ggplot(eggproduction, aes(x = observed_month, y = n_eggs/n_hens)) +
  geom_point() +
  labs(
    title = "Number of eggs laid per hen in 2020",
    subtitle = "*Assuming every hen laid the same number of eggs",
    x = "Date",
    y = "Number of Eggs"
  )

title: TidyTuesday #1
text:
Data was sourced from Numbats in Australia by jonthegeek on Github

# Packages
library(tidyverse)
library(ggplot2)

# Data
numbats <- readr::read_csv('https://raw.githubusercontent.com/rfordatascience/tidytuesday/master/data/2023/2023-03-07/numbats.csv')

# Filtering Data
numbats |>
  select(decimalLatitude, decimalLongitude, scientificName) |>
  filter(scientificName == "Myrmecobius fasciatus")

# A tibble: 787 × 3
   decimalLatitude decimalLongitude scientificName       
             <dbl>            <dbl> <chr>                
 1           -37.6             146. Myrmecobius fasciatus
 2           -35.1             150. Myrmecobius fasciatus
 3           -35               118. Myrmecobius fasciatus
 4           -34.7             118. Myrmecobius fasciatus
 5           -34.6             117. Myrmecobius fasciatus
 6           -34.6             117. Myrmecobius fasciatus
 7           -34.6             118. Myrmecobius fasciatus
 8           -34.6             117. Myrmecobius fasciatus
 9           -34.6             117. Myrmecobius fasciatus
10           -34.6             117. Myrmecobius fasciatus
# ℹ 777 more rows

# Making Plots
ggplot(data = numbats, aes(x = decimalLatitude, y = decimalLongitude)) +
  geom_point() +
  labs(title = "Coordinates of 787 Numbats (Myrmecobius fasciatus)", x = "Coordinate Latitude", y = "Coordinate Longitude")
